description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen to work within a medical education team, looking after the needs of medical students from Nottingham University whilst on placement at Derby.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This will involve booking teaching sessions both live and on MST, monitoring and trouble shooting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Arrangements for students receiving swipe access and alarms as well as computer log ons and assisting them in using these resources.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Knowledge of Excel spread sheets, MST, and Attend Anywhere if possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Also being able to use systems for paying Expert Patients and Role Players such as raising invoices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The person will need to work from base predominantly as allocating rooms and laptops for the students to use is a vital part of the job at present. Some work from home may be feasible, however.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;David Hackett, Team manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;david.hackett@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07426 084425&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alexa Sidwell, alexa.sidwell@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
